snippet.textDisplay:
tragic romance Mirza–Sahiban.

“Sutte ke teer tūṭenge.”🎶
In the qissa (ballad), Mirza elopes with Sahiban. While he rests under a tree, Sahiban sees her brothers approaching and, to prevent bloodshed, breaks Mirza’s arrows(teer tut gaye). When the brothers arrive, Mirza wakes to find himself unarmed and is killed; Sahiban then takes her own life (in some tellings she throws herself on an arrow).
